      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FENWAY PARK (6) was responsible for a very good effort last time over 1690m at this track, finishing second and just a head from the winner. Stepping up a level this time but on his best form he is capable of another big performance. ALIZA HILL (1) settled in the leading division then took control of the race and scored in a 1770m race at Albury last start, arriving 4.5 metres ahead of her rivals. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run and her last-start form is good enough to win a race of this calibre. YA BOTTOM DOLLAR (2) was responsible for a better effort last time out when runner-up over 1650m at Bendigo. Should run a big race. KING SAINT (3) has drawn to advantage and should give backers a great sight.",
